5px;">The board</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is an exaggeration, but a useful on=
e, to say that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/274=
85978.273602/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE0MT=
gwOTEvMDAwMTE0MDM2MTIyMDE0MDQ5L255MjAwMDE5MjF4M19kZWYxNGEuaHRtI3RCT0Q/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB4f0d70f3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Twitter=E2=80=99s board of directors<=
/a> is made up of 11 people who don=E2=80=99t use Twitter and don=E2=80=99t=
 own any Twitter stock. Actually one member of the board =E2=80=94=C2=A0tho=
ugh he is scheduled to step down next month =E2=80=94=C2=A0is Jack Dorsey, =
a founder of Twitter, who (1) owns 2.4% of the company, (2) uses the produc=
t and (3) <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27485978=
.273602/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMi8wNC8xOC90d2l0dGVycy1leC1jZW8tY3J=
