ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">does not seem to get along</a> wi=
th the other directors. The other 10 directors <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27485978.273602/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9Bcm=
NoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE0MDM2MTIyMDE0MDQ5L255MjAwMDE5M=
jF4M19kZWYxNGEuaHRtI3RTT0M/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc6b205e6" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">all o=
wn=C2=A0a little stock</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0about 0.2% of the company, total,=
 among them =E2=80=94=C2=A0and I=E2=80=99m sure they all have Twitter accou=
nts and tweet occasionally.[3] But if your model of Twitter=E2=80=99s board=
 was =E2=80=9Cthis is a collection of=C2=A0fancy important smart successful=
 business and tech people who have no particular connection to Twitter,=E2=
=80=9D that would, I think, be mostly fine? Some public tech companies have=
 boards made up of, like, the founder and a handful of venture capitalists =
who backed the company from the beginning and are passionate believers in t=
he company=E2=80=99s product and mission. Twitter=E2=80=99s board isn=E2=80=
=99t like that.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter is a strange compan=
y; it has enormous influence on politics and culture but is not great at ma=
king money. It has a lot of power as a venue of public discussion, and ther=
e is a lot of debate among Twitter=E2=80=99s employees and users, and among=
 politicians and regulators, about how it should use that power. Elon Musk =
certainly cares about this stuff, and has explicitly said that he wants to =
buy Twitter not for economic reasons but for =E2=80=9Cfree speech.=E2=80=9D=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could imagine a board of directors of =
a publicly traded company with an important social purpose=C2=A0<em>caring =
about that purpose=C2=A0</em>as it decides whether or not to sell the compa=
ny. You could imagine Twitter=E2=80=99s board thinking things like =E2=80=
=9CTwitter will be better for the world if Elon Musk owns it than if it is =
owned by the public,=E2=80=9D[4] or =E2=80=9CTwitter will be worse for the =
world if Elon Musk owns it.=E2=80=9D You could imagine the board declining =
to sell to Musk if it thinks his ownership would be bad. Or you could imagi=
ne it negotiating some sort of protections for the product =E2=80=94=C2=A0s=
ome commitment by Musk not to do some bad things, not to censor his critics=
 or whatever, or=C2=A0some independent review board to protect the product =
under Musk=E2=80=99s ownership =E2=80=94=C2=A0before agreeing to sell. (Of =
course it is hard to imagine Musk=C2=A0<em>agreeing=C2=A0</em>to that; he w=
ants Twitter because it is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/27485978.273602/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydG=
ljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMDQvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWJvdWdodC1zb21lLXR3aXR0ZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEM=
DQyNTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXIm=
dXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNDI1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cC51fa5323" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> his favorite toy</a> and he wants it to work exactly =
the way he wants.)</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, to be clear, if the=
 board did any of this, the goal would not be to preserve value for the sha=
reholders. If Elon Musk buys Twitter for $54.20 per share, Twitter=E2=80=99=
s public shareholders will get $54.20 and won=E2=80=99t own Twitter anymore=
. If Musk=E2=80=99s actions crash the value of the company, or increase it,=
 that has nothing to do with the public shareholders; they=E2=80=99ll be go=
